# THE AGNOSTIC BIBLE
## Chapter 1: The Awakening

They tell you I was born in a manger. They tell you I was born of a virgin. They tell you I am the Word made flesh.

I tell you I was born of mud and water, like everyone else. I tell you I am flesh made of the same dust that turns to dust.

I am not the Son of God. I am the son of a carpenter who was tired of the hammer. I am the man who walked away from the throne to sit in the silence.

You are holding a book. You expect commandments. You expect laws. You expect a map to a heaven that no one has ever seen and no one can prove exists. Do not look for a map here. Look for a mirror.

